    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with **Pete Crow-Armstrong** serving as our highest-value play, boasting a massive 82.12 score. Facing Sasaki (xERA 5.52), **Pete Crow-Armstrong** benefits from an elite matchup profile and favorable wind conditions that amplify his base projections, making him an essential start despite the lower order placement. Similarly, **Junior Caminero** (73.52) and **Trea Turner** (68.85) provide strong anchors for the lineup; **Trea Turner** is locked into the leadoff spot against Elder, and his 68.85 score reflects the high-floor efficiency we demand. While **Yordan Alvarez** faces a tougher L/L matchup against Weathers, his elite xwOBA maintains his status as a recommended start at 62.54.\n\nStrategic platoon and park adjustments played a significant role in today\u2019s construction, most notably for **Caleb Durbin**, whose 16% park factor bump keeps his score at a respectable 57.25 despite the lower order slot. Conversely, **Dillon Dingler** is our most marginal start at 43.96; his score is hampered by a significant negative platoon adjustment, but he remains in the lineup due to the lack of viable alternatives at C1. The most difficult bench decision involved **Victor Scott II**, who just missed the cut with a 39.50 score. While **Victor Scott II** offers the stolen base profile the Zebras covet, his matchup against a difficult arm in Woo, combined with a bottom-of-the-order assignment, dropped him just below our 40.0 efficiency floor. \n\nWe continue to monitor the status of **Christian Yelich** and **Lars Nootbaar**, both of whom remain sidelined on the IL, while **Zac Veen** remains unavailable in the minors. As we navigate the schedule, we will keep a close eye on any late-inning wind shifts that could further benefit the heavy-hitters like **Kyle Schwarber** (65.76), whose elite xwOBA of .402 and prime order position provide high confidence for today's contest. We remain disciplined regarding our game caps, benching players like **Victor Scott II** to ensure we maintain roster flexibility throughout the remainder of the week.",
